  \Phi is a class and (if \Nat is a set then \Phi is a set) and for all v0, (v0 is an element of \Phi iff (v0 is an element of \Nat and v0 is an object and n \NATmul m \NATmul v0 is equal to n \NATmul m \NATmul v0))
  \NATzero is an element of \Phi
  Proof:
    n \NATmul m \NATmul \NATzero is equal to n \NATmul \NATzero and n \NATmul \NATzero is equal to \NATzero and \NATzero is equal to n \NATmul m \NATmul \NATzero
  Qed.
  for all v0, (if v0 is an element of \Phi then v0 \NATplus \NATone is an element of \Phi)
  Proof:
    k' is an element of \Phi
    n \NATmul m \NATmul k' \NATplus \NATone is equal to n \NATmul m \NATmul k' \NATplus m and n \NATmul m \NATmul k' \NATplus m is equal to n \NATmul m \NATmul k' \NATplus n \NATmul m and n \NATmul m \NATmul k' \NATplus n \NATmul m is equal to n \NATmul m \NATmul k' \NATplus n \NATmul m and n \NATmul m \NATmul k' \NATplus n \NATmul m is equal to n \NATmul m \NATmul k' \NATplus n \NATmul m \NATmul \NATone and n \NATmul m \NATmul k' \NATplus n \NATmul m \NATmul \NATone is equal to n \NATmul m \NATmul k' \NATplus \NATone
  Qed.
  for all v0, (if v0 is a natural number then v0 is an element of \Phi)
  n \NATmul m \NATmul k is equal to n \NATmul m \NATmul k
Qed.

Theorem (commutativity_of_multiplication):
  for all v0, (for all v1, (if v1 is a natural number and v0 is a natural number then v1 \NATmul v0 is equal to v0 \NATmul v1))
Proof:
  \Phi is a class and (if \Nat is a set then \Phi is a set) and for all v0, (v0 is an element of \Phi iff (v0 is an element of \Nat and v0 is an object and n \NATmul v0 is equal to v0 \NATmul n))
  \NATzero is an element of \Phi
  Proof:
    \Psi is a class and (if \Nat is a set then \Psi is a set) and for all v0, (v0 is an element of \Psi iff (v0 is an element of \Nat and v0 is an object and v0 \NATmul \NATzero is equal to \NATzero \NATmul v0))
    \NATzero is an element of \Psi
    for all v0, (if v0 is an element of \Psi then v0 \NATplus \NATone is an element of \Psi)
    Proof:
      n' is an element of \Psi
      n' \NATplus \NATone \NATmul \NATzero is equal to \NATzero and \NATzero is equal to n' \NATmul \NATzero and n' \NATmul \NATzero is equal to \NATzero \NATmul n' and \NATzero \NATmul n' is equal to \NATzero \NATmul n' \NATplus \NATzero and \NATzero \NATmul n' \NATplus \NATzero is equal to \NATzero \NATmul n' \NATplus \NATone
    Qed.
    for all v0, (if v0 is a natural number then v0 is an element of \Psi)
    n \NATmul \NATzero is equal to \NATzero \NATmul n
  Qed.
  \NATone is an element of \Phi
  Proof:
    \Theta is a class and (if \Nat is a set then \Theta is a set) and for all v0, (v0 is an element of \Theta iff (v0 is an element of \Nat and v0 is an object and v0 \NATmul \NATone is equal to \NATone \NATmul v0))
    \NATzero is an element of \Theta
    for all v0, (if v0 is an element of \Theta then v0 \NATplus \NATone is an element of \Theta)
    Proof:
      n' is an element of \Theta
      n' \NATplus \NATone \NATmul \NATone is equal to n' \NATmul \NATone \NATplus \NATone and n' \NATmul \NATone \NATplus \NATone is equal to \NATone \NATmul n' \NATplus \NATone and \NATone \NATmul n' \NATplus \NATone is equal to \NATone \NATmul n' \NATplus \NATone
    Qed.
    for all v0, (if v0 is a natural number then v0 is an element of \Theta)
    n \NATmul \NATone is equal to \NATone \NATmul n
  Qed.
  for all v0, (if v0 is an element of \Phi then v0 \NATplus \NATone is an element of \Phi)
  Proof:
    m' is an element of \Phi
    n \NATmul m' \NATplus \NATone is equal to n \NATmul m' \NATplus n \NATmul \NATone and n \NATmul m' \NATplus n \NATmul \NATone is equal to m' \NATmul n \NATplus \NATone \NATmul n and m' \NATmul n \NATplus \NATone \NATmul n is equal to \NATone \NATmul n \NATplus m' \NATmul n and \NATone \NATmul n \NATplus m' \NATmul n is equal to \NATone \NATplus m' \NATmul n and \NATone \NATplus m' \NATmul n is equal to m' \NATplus \NATone \NATmul n
    Proof:
