          l is positive
        Qed.
      Qed.
    Qed.
  Qed.
  for all v0, (if v0 is a natural number then v0 is an element of \Phi)
  n \NATless m or n is equal to m or m \NATless n
Qed.

Theorem:
  for all v0, (for all v1, (if v1 is a natural number and v0 is a natural number then (it is wrong that v1 \NATless v0 iff v0 \NATleq v1)))
Proof:
